REFTEXT: MRAP (Mine Resistant, Ambush Protected) are armoured personnel carriers that are specifically designed to withstand ambushes, mines or improvised explosive devices.
Units travelling inside an MRAP vehicle have a greater chance of survival when their vehicle is destroyed.
Standoff Armour takes the form of rigid metal skirts fitted in front of the main armour of a vehicle. These skirts interfere with incoming HEAT warheads reducing their effectiveness.
Standoff Armour provides additional Armour to the front and sides of a vehicle when hit by a HEAT weapon. Armour Values from 1-5 gain +3 Armour, 6-10 gain +2 Armour, >10 gain +1 Armour.

Reactive Armour provides additional Armour to the front and sides of a vehicle when hit by a HEAT weapon. Armour Values from 1-5 gain +5 Armour, 6-10 gain +4 Armour, 10-15 gain +3 Armour, 16-20 gain +2 Armour, >21 gain +1 Armour.
Thermal Sights use the infrared radiation emitted by objects to produce images showing temperature. These allow for targets to be more easily spotted.
Thermal Sights provide a 10% aimtime reduction and one level of optics for non recon units.
Advanced Thermals use the infrared radiation emitted by objects to produce images like standard Thermal Sights but with increased resolution. This makes target acquisition easier.
Advanced Thermals provide a 20% aimtime reduction and one level of optics for non recon units.
This unit is an large Unmanned Aerial Vehicle, a drone piloted from the ground by an operator and used for reconnaissance or ground attack.

Due to their small size and slow speed, UAVs are targeted by a weapons helicopter range rather than its aircraft range and enemies targeting a UAV have a penalty to their accuracy. In addition, UAVs do not suffer from stress. Large UAVs fly at high altitudes reducing the effectiveness of ground based AA systems.
This unit is an Unmanned Aerial Vehicle, a drone piloted from the ground by an operator and used for reconnaissance or ground attack.

Due to their small size and slow speed, UAVs are targeted by a weapons helicopter range rather than its aircraft range and enemies targeting a UAV have a penalty to their accuracy. In addition, UAVs do not suffer from stress and have greater stealth than a regular aircraft.
Active Protection System (APS) is a countermeasure device designed to defeat anti-tank weapons from destroying a vehicle.
Active Protection Systems provide +2 HP and reduce the chance of being hit by anti-tank missiles.

Active Protection System (APS) is a countermeasure device designed to defeat anti-tank weapons from destroying a vehicle. These weapons will attempt to intercept incoming enemy missiles. Faster missiles are harder to intercept than slower missiles.
